==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hick
<hw>hick</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person who is not very intelligent or
interested in culture; a hayseed.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> yokel, rube, yahoo, hayseed, bumpkin,
chawbacon.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hick</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: hick
<hw>hick</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>rural. Opposite of
<ant>urban</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>characteristic of rural people, especially those not
knowledgeable about matters outside their locality; <as>as,
<ex>hick</ex> ideas; a <ex>hick</ex> town</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bumpkinly, rustic, unsophisticated.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hickie</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>hickey</ent>⟦br⟧
